m Louis’s trial until the fall of Robespierre. A highly original work of historical analysis, political theory, literary criticism, and intellectual history, The Terror of Natural Right challenges prevailing assumptions of the Terror to offer a new perspective on the Revolutionary period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  arepublicanism, french revolution, france, politics, political ideology, citizenship, nation state, republic, laws, rights, government, governing, radical change, social changes, liberal democracy, democratic representation, freedom, revolutionaries, humanity, jacobins, reign of terror, massacres, public executions, treason accusations, republican theory, history, historical, 18th century, violence, natural right.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022618438840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226184401423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226184401/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles